{
  "texts": [
    "Consequently, GNNs can analyze structural relationships within fossil assemblies or between different parts of fragmented fossils.",
    "Additionally, GNNs could be applied to analyze the spatial and temporal relationships between different fossils within an assemblage, identifying patterns in how species coexisted or how ecosystems evolved over time.",
    "By capturing these relationships, GNNs can help paleontologists make more informed inferences about the biology and ecology of ancient organisms, ultimately leading to more accurate reconstructions of past life and environments.",
    "This approach is particularly valuable for interpreting complex or fragmented fossil records where traditional methods fall short.",
    "It enhances the ability to accurately reconstruct ancient life forms and ecosystems, improving our understanding of past biodiversity and ecological dynamics."
  ]
}